        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-06T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-09-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="856" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d856">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 P.W./9–646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-06T18:00:00-04:00">September 6, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>721. In confidential conversation here in Dept. with Russian representative on
                    Far Eastern Commission in regard to reparations from Japan, the representative
                    has stated that “negotiations are proceeding between China and the USSR” in
                    regard to “war booty” which has not been removed from Manchuria. Please make
                    discreet inquiry as to whether there are in fact any such negotiations and if
                    there are endeavor to ascertain their character.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clayton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
